      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p>1. In the OUT context, insert a denoise node and connect your RenderMan ROP node to the denoise node.  <br/><br/></p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544645311/RenderMan_Houdini_Denoiser1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433139825&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544645311/RenderMan_Houdini_Denoiser1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433139825&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544645323\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Houdini_Denoiser1.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544645311\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"dce8f41b-fc95-4675-ba3a-bd9cb0fa1566\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><br/><br/>2. Under Images In the RenderMan ROP, untick <strong>as RGBA</strong> and select <strong>Denoise</strong><br/><br/><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544645311/RenderMan_Houdini_Denoiser2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433139825&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544645311/RenderMan_Houdini_Denoiser2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433139825&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544645326\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Houdini_Denoiser2.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544645311\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"8336374d-211f-4eb4-a2fe-bb12024a2489\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><br/><br/><br/></p><p>3.   Select the <strong>denoise</strong> node and set mode type, output location, Asymmetry, Flow and debug options, and once ready to render, press the Denoise button.<br/><br/><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544645311/RenderMan_Houdini_Denoiser3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433140073&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544645311/RenderMan_Houdini_Denoiser3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433140073&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544645332\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Houdini_Denoiser3.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544645311\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"6dfc9bcb-57f2-4b92-8215-06f83e34f558\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><br/><br/><br/>To render the frame(s), click Denoise and Houdini will then render the frame(s) and once all the frames have been rendered, the denoise process will begin.</p><p /><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"59aea1b2-c0f8-406a-9c5d-c115e613acf3\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><h3 id=\"DenoiserinHoudini-Gotcha\">Gotcha</h3><p>Whilst it might sound obvious, always make sure you add the $F4 to your filename, otherwise, the denoiser will fail, even if you are rendering a single frame.</p></div></div><p /><p />"
    }
